index 0000000..7595607
--- /dev/null
+++ b/findings.md
@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@
+- src/sync.py:14 `range(total_count // PAGE_SIZE)` uses floor division, so the final partial page is never fetched (and no rows at all when total_count < PAGE_SIZE), silently dropping staged users.
+- src/sync.py:24 `seen=[]` is a mutable default argument shared across all calls, so IDs synced in a previous call are wrongly skipped as duplicates in later calls.
+- src/sync.py:31 the user ID is appended to `seen` before the sync attempt, so a user whose sync fails is permanently marked as already-synced and never retried.
+- src/sync.py:35 email and id are interpolated into the UPDATE via f-string instead of bound parameters, introducing SQL injection and breaking on emails containing a quote (e.g. o'brien@x.com).
+- src/sync.py:38 the bare `except Exception: pass` silently swallows all sync errors (previously logged), hiding failures while the partial work is still committed.
+- src/report.py:7 the early `return 0` when users is empty leaves the file opened at line 5 unclosed (resource leak) because the `with` block was removed.
+- src/report.py:11 `user["email"].lower().split("@")[1]` crashes on rows where email is None (schema notes say email is nullable) and on addresses without an "@" (IndexError).
